posts.subject: Suspicious Minds
posts.body:
I understand that much on the internet is untrue. But I also remember a time when a professor described how researchers were dumbfounded by the results they were getting during multiple corporation experiments.

"Rumors" on the grapevine were usually of higher quality and accuracy than corporate information released. Furthermore, inaccurate, untruthful information was usually purged from the grapevine within 24hrs.

These were not the results they had been expecting. Likely puzzles them to this day.

They had uncovered a brutish truth. Completely by accident.

So how can we reconcile internet misinformation with the superior "parity" demonstrated by informal corporate networks?

Just would like to know the truth. It's dismaying that we may never know.
